h2.under 2) Patagonia's images
p In the 1980s all outdoor fashion catalogs looked the same.
p Paid models. Fake hikes.
p Patagonia’s founder, Yvon Chouinard, was sick of it. So he placed a note in their catalog asking customers to send in real photos.
p Suddenly Patagonia stood out. They still only use real customers today.
